for a Sunday in the Season after Pentecost according to the Book of Common Prayer (p. 75ff.)
Find the lessons for today using the calendar here
 The Officiant begins the service with a sentence of Scripture.  Watch, for you do not know when the master of the house will come, in the evening, or at midnight, or at cockcrow, or in the morning, lest he come suddenly and find you asleep.
